            <mtext>electric</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>q</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"bold">E</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \mathbf {F} _=
{\text{electric}}=3Dq\mathbf {E} .}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d694aac8114153241a5251d7a3cb0279ad6a4b79" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.671ex; width:13.606ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
mathbf {F} _{\text{electric}}=3Dq\mathbf {E} .}"></span>
</p><p>The second term is the magnetic force:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Griffiths3=
ed_13-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magne=
tic_field#cite_note-Griffiths3ed-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \mathbf {F} _{\text{magnetic}}=3Dq(\mathbf {v} \times \mathbf {=
B} ).}">
