tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/50803d43052cc495a33b72b65efb2c383fc40cb4" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.338ex; width:21.286ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
oint _{S}\mu _{0}\mathbf {M} \cdot \mathrm {d} \mathbf {A} =3D-q_{\mathrm {=
M} },}"></span>
where the integral is a closed surface integral over the closed surface <sp=
an class=3D"texhtml"><i>S</i></span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>q</i><s=
ub>M</sub></span> is the "magnetic charge" (in units of <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnetic_flux" title=3D"Magnetic flux">magnetic flux<=
/a>) enclosed by <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>S</i></span>. (A closed surface=
 completely surrounds a region with no holes to let any field lines escape.=
) The negative sign occurs because the magnetization field moves from south=
 to north.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"H-field_and_magnetic_materi=
als">H-field and magnetic materials</h3></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
